UNITED STATES of America ex rel. Lillian AIMI, Next Friend of Michael Aimi, Relator-Appellant, v. Edward CORSI, Commissioner of Immigration at Ellis Island, New York Harbor, New York, Respondent-Appellee. No. 288. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. Jan. 22, 1934. Sol Woronoff, of New York City, for appellant. Martin Conboy, U. S. Atty., of New York City (Bronson Goddard, Asst. U. S. Atty., of New York City, of counsel), for appellee.

Before MANTON, AUGUSTUS N.. HAND, and CHASE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

_ Order affirmed.
